.
                                         CAPE TOWN - An Eastern Cape mother and son have died in a fire. Police say the blaze broke during the early hours of Sunday at the Endlovini informal settlement near Port Elizabeth. The mother, 73-year-old Nolulamile Mbengashe and her son, 46-year-old Lwandile, succumbed their wounds and were found dead in their home.   The police’s Andre Beetge said: “It is suspected that the son was busy making food when the fire started; an inquest docket has been opened.”